title: About
text:
Hello!
I’m James Ashmore, the creator of Bioinformer.
My goal is to share insights and experiences from the bioinformatics field. In my free time, I enjoy playing the electric guitar, Warhammer, and Arkham horror boardgames. Through Bioinformer, I aim to make scientific concepts engaging and accessible to everyone, from experts to curious minds, in the field of computational life sciences.

title: About
text:
I’m James Ashmore, the creator of Bioinformer.
I blend skills from computational biology, bioinformatics, programming, and data analysis. My academic background includes a Master’s in Computational Biology and a PhD in Regenerative Medicine. Currently, I work as a bioinformatics consultant at Excelra. My goal is to share insights and experiences from the bioinformatics field. In my free time, I enjoy playing the electric guitar, Warhammer, and Arkham horror boardgames. Through Bioinformer, I aim to make scientific concepts engaging and accessible to everyone, from experts to curious minds, in the field of computational life sciences.
